        <dc:title>Pseudo-Newtonian potential for charged particle in Kerr–Newman geometry</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>We consider the equatorial circular motion of a test particle of speciﬁc charge q m in the Kerr–Newman geometry of a rotating charged black hole. We ﬁnd the particle’s conserved energy and conserved projection of the angular momentum on the black hole’s axis of rotation as corrections, in leading order of q/m, to the corresponding energy and angular momentum of a neutral particle. We determine the centripetal force acting on the test particle and, consequently, we ﬁnd a classical pseudoNewtonian potential with which one can mimic this general relativistic problem.</dcterms:abstract>
